Sentencas: Tubular direct carbon SOFCs (solid oxide fuel cells) supported by YSZ (Y2O3 stabilized ZrO2) electrolyte are fabricated by slurry-casting, slurry-dipping and sintering processes with La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-10 mol.% Gd2O3 doped CeO2 (LSCF-10GDC) as the cathode.
Titulo: Tubular direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells with molten antimony anode and refueling feasibility

Sentencas: Their electrochemical performance is examined at temperatures from 700 to 800 degrees C using molten antimony (Sb) anode and activated carbon fuel.
Titulo: Tubular direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells with molten antimony anode and refueling feasibility

Sentencas: The ohmic resistance of the cell is between 1.01 and 0.37 Omega cm(2) mainly originated from the thick YSZ electrolyte (150 mu m); the polarization resistance ranges from 0.22 to 0.06 Omega cm(2).
Titulo: Tubular direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells with molten antimony anode and refueling feasibility

Sentencas: The maximum power density at 800 degrees C is 304 mW cm(-2) and can be greatly increased by using a thinner and/or more conductive electrolyte.
Titulo: Tubular direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells with molten antimony anode and refueling feasibility

Sentencas: With 1 g activated carbon as the fuel, the cell performance is stable at 200 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C for more than 6 h by chemical consumption (oxidization) of the carbon, which reduces the electrochemically formed Sb2O3 to Sb.
Titulo: Tubular direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells with molten antimony anode and refueling feasibility

Sentencas: The cell performance decreases as the fuel is used up and is recovered by refueling.
Titulo: Tubular direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells with molten antimony anode and refueling feasibility
